## Eat Smart

Eat Smart is a Django web application for healthy meal planning. Users maintain a health profile, build weekly meal plans (with optional background generation from calorie and protein targets), browse recipes, and aggregate shopping lists from their plans. Nutrition coaches and staff manage the shared ingredient catalog and recipes. Standard users consume that catalog for their own plans and create shopping list.


## Technical information


Framework -  Django 5.2
API Django REST Framework 3.16|
Database - PostgreSQL (via psycopg 3.x)
Configuration - django-environ` (.env` file)
Background queue - django-rq + Redis
Media - Pillow for image uploads (e.g. recipe photos)

All versions are listed in requirements.txt.


## Project structure

EatSmart/                 # Django project package
  settings.py             # Installed apps, DB, RQ, REST_FRAMEWORK, AUTH_USER_MODEL
  urls.py                 # Root URL routing
  error_views.py          # Custom 500 handler
  workers.py              # RQ worker class (Windows-friendly)
accounts/                 # Custom user (AppUser), profile, auth URLs, middleware
recipes/                  # Recipe models, views, forms, DRF API
ingredients/              # Ingredient & recipe-line models, catalog views, API, mixins
mealplans/                # Weekly meal plans, RQ job for target-based generation
shopping/                 # Shopping lists derived from meal plans
nutrition/                # Nutrition calculations and services (no ORM models)
templates/                # Global templates, base layout, partials (navbar, footer)
static/                   # CSS, images
media/                    # User-uploaded files (created at runtime; not in git)
manage.py
requirements.txt
README.md                 # This file


##App capabilities

accounts - Email-based AppUser, UserProfile, registration/login/logout, profile edit, navigation context, health-profile middleware
recipes - Recipe CRUD (access controlled), recipe detail/list, recipe–ingredient lines, is_public visibility for anonymous users, recipe REST API
ingredients - Ingredient catalog, RecipeIngredient links, CanManageFoodMixin, ingredient REST API
mealplans - Per-user weekly plans, optional RQ-backed generation from targets
shopping - Shopping list regeneration from meal plans, “bought” flags
nutrition - Services including calculation of recipe calories and protein, meal-plan matching helpers with target goal for user and template tags